history.text: hey there!
HELLO HOW ARE U?
Good thanks! How are you?
GREAT! SO HAVE YOU READ THE DOC?
Yes
I love Aaron Sorkin's writing. The American President and The West Wing are two of my favourites - do you like this writing?
i NEVER KNEW ANYTHING ABOUT THIS FILM OR ABOUT ZUCKERBERG
I HAVEN'T HEARD OF HIM ACTUALLY.. BUT I LOVE THE WEST WING!

HAVE YOU READ "THE ACCIDENTAL BILLIONAIRES"
?

It follows Facebook the early years in a way. Originally it was set up on one campus in the US and then spread across the world to what we eventually know Facebook as today. I think I got my FB account around Christmas 2006 and hardly anyone else was on it!
DID YOU HAVE A MYSPACE AS WELL?
No I haven't read the book. I saw the film before even realising it was from a book originally. Normally I'm quite hot on trying to read the book before seeing a film adaptation.
I BECAME SOMEWHAT ADDICTED TO SOCIAL MEDIA DURING THE MYSPACE CRAZE.
I did have MySpace too! It was the place to be at the time! I learnt basic HTML by messing about with my MySpace profile - I believe it's still ive somewhere!
IM NOT SO MUCH ANYMORE
still live even!
LOL.. I STILL CAN LOG ON TO MINE. SO ARE YOU A STUDENT?
So the book was written but i think it was written by someone on the outside looking in rather than someone actually involved in Facebook.
No I graduated in 2007. I'm in my 30s now and feel very old when I talk about video cassettes or a Walkman!

SO WHAT HAPPEN WITH THE LAWSUITS AND FACEBOOK
?
IM INTERESTED NOW AND WANT TO READ THE BOOK!
JUSTIN TIMBERLAKE ACTS??

So the Winklevoss brothers for a long time tried to make out that Zuckerberg had stolen the idea from them. I think it came down to that Zuckerberg had the brains to do it whereas the Winklevoss brothers didn't or something like that. I think I last saw the film in about 2011 if not before then. I remember not going to see it at the cinema, then watching it at my friend's house. He was the film nerd of our friendship group so knew all the information.
Timberlake - he does. I think this was one of his first movie roles.
I'm wrong - it wasn't his first role. He'd been in other films before then - voicing characters in animations.
THE FILM GOT DECENT RATINGS.. EVEN THOUGH I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT A METACRITIC SCORE IS..

Metacritic is another website for movie ratings - it picks up ratings from other websites and then combines them. I generally avoid movie reviews - I always find that they say a film sucks and I love it, or they say it's amazing and it's as boring as watching paint dry! I watched the Social Network once and haven't watch it again.
"THE WORLD IN SUPERMAN'S ABSENCE"? FIRST PARAGRAPH.. WHAT IS THAT REFERENCING DO YOU KNOW? SORRY IM ASKING YOU SO MANY QUESTIONS!!
YOUR VERY BRIGHT!
YOU'RE I MEAN
I have no idea - it's almost like it's a misprint! I'm pretty sure there's no mention of Superman in the movie but i could be wrong!
Thank you! I like to think that I'd fit in with the Nerd Geek Girls in shows like NCIS and Criminal Minds etc
GREAT SHOWS!!
FACEMASH?? I WONDER IF ITS STILL A WORKING WEBSITE

Indeed! Abby and Garcia are my favourites! I used to work in an office and on one occasion when I fixed the photocopier for like the 100th time I accidentally shouted "I'n the King of the Lab" of course I then had to explaiin to my colleagues the reference! (It's from Bones if you didn't know)
Not by the looks of it but it does have it's own Facebook Page!

LOVE BONES AS WELL!!! THAT HILARIOUS!! THERE WAS A RUMOR GOING AROUND FOR THE LONGEST THAT ABBY HAD DIED! I WAS SO UPSET BUT IT ENDED
 UP BEING A RUMOR..
Always Google when those rumours circulate! People share on Facebook and don't check the facts.
Well the button has lit up which means I think we've had our conversation now. I need to head to bed as it is now 11:30pm here!
THE CRITICAL RESPONSE IS TO MUCH ." LACING AND SCATHING WITH AN ACHING SADNESS"  REALLY?
YES I GUESS SO!

NICE CHATTING WITH YOU!!
'
GN
Night night! Have a good week!

uid2response.feedback: However there is one sentence about Superman which seems completely out of place.
